cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.Distributed, cs.SY, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper focuses on the security of a payment network and proposes a novel approach to mitigate against Byzantine failures. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses a decentralised network of trusted execution environments (TEEs) and how they can be used to improve the performance of payment networks. 
3. cs.Distributed (Distributed Computing) - The paper proposes a distributed payment network that uses TEEs to secure collateral funds in payment channels. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the design and implementation of Teechain, a payment network system. 
5. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper may touch on programming languages used to implement Teechain or the design of smart contracts used in the payment network.
